{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "student-manager-collection",
    "name": "Student Manager API",
    "description": "CAP Java Student Manager OData V4 API collection.\n\nThis collection includes CRUD operations for the Students entity and various OData query examples.\n\n## Authentication\n- **Local**: Basic Auth with mock users (admin/admin or user/user)\n- **Cloud**: OAuth2 via XSUAA (configure in environment)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "{{baseUrl}}",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "basic",
    "basic": [
      {
        "key": "username",
        "value": "{{username}}",
        "type": "string"
      },
      {
        "key": "password",
        "value": "{{password}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Service Metadata",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Service Document",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the OData service document listing all available entity sets."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Metadata ($metadata)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/$metadata",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "$metadata"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the OData EDMX metadata document describing the entity model."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "OData service metadata and documentation endpoints."
    },
    {
      "name": "Students CRUD",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get All Students",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"]
            },
            "description": "Retrieve all students from the database."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Student by ID",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students({{studentId}})",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students({{studentId}})"]
            },
            "description": "Retrieve a single student by their UUID.\n\nExample IDs from seed data:\n- 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111 (Alice)\n- 22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222 (Bob)\n- 33333333-3333-3333-3333-333333333333 (Carol)"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Student",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"David\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Brown\",\n  \"email\": \"david.brown@example.com\",\n  \"dateOfBirth\": \"1998-07-15\",\n  \"status\": \"ACTIVE\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new student. The ID will be auto-generated (UUID).\n\n**Required fields:** firstName, lastName, email\n**Optional fields:** dateOfBirth, status (defaults to 'ACTIVE')\n\n**Validation:** Email must contain '@' character."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Student (PATCH)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"INACTIVE\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students({{studentId}})",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students({{studentId}})"]
            },
            "description": "Partially update a student. Only the provided fields will be updated.\n\nCommon use case: Update student status to 'INACTIVE'."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Student (PUT)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"David\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Brown-Updated\",\n  \"email\": \"david.updated@example.com\",\n  \"dateOfBirth\": \"1998-07-15\",\n  \"status\": \"ACTIVE\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students({{studentId}})",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students({{studentId}})"]
            },
            "description": "Fully replace a student record. All fields should be provided."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Student",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students({{studentId}})",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students({{studentId}})"]
            },
            "description": "Delete a student by ID. Returns 204 No Content on success."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Create, Read, Update, Delete operations for Students entity."
    },
    {
      "name": "OData Queries",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "$select - Select Specific Fields",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$select=firstName,lastName,email",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$select",
                  "value": "firstName,lastName,email"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Return only specific fields to reduce payload size."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "$filter - Active Students",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$filter=status eq 'ACTIVE'",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$filter",
                  "value": "status eq 'ACTIVE'"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Filter students by status = ACTIVE."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "$filter - By Last Name (contains)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$filter=contains(lastName,'son')",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$filter",
                  "value": "contains(lastName,'son')"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Filter students whose last name contains 'son' (e.g., Johnson)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "$filter - Born After Date",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$filter=dateOfBirth gt 2000-01-01",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$filter",
                  "value": "dateOfBirth gt 2000-01-01"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Filter students born after January 1, 2000."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "$orderby - Sort by Last Name",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$orderby=lastName asc",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$orderby",
                  "value": "lastName asc"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Sort students alphabetically by last name (ascending)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "$orderby - Sort by Created Date (desc)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$orderby=createdAt desc",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$orderby",
                  "value": "createdAt desc"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Sort students by creation date, most recent first."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "$top & $skip - Pagination",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$top=2&$skip=1",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$top",
                  "value": "2"
                },
                {
                  "key": "$skip",
                  "value": "1"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Paginate results: skip first record, take next 2."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "$count - Get Total Count",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students/$count",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students", "$count"]
            },
            "description": "Get the total number of students (returns integer)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "$count=true - Include Count in Response",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$count=true&$top=2",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$count",
                  "value": "true"
                },
                {
                  "key": "$top",
                  "value": "2"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Include @odata.count in the response along with paginated data."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Combined Query",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/odata/v4/StudentService/Students?$filter=status eq 'ACTIVE'&$select=firstName,lastName,email&$orderby=lastName asc&$top=10",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["odata", "v4", "StudentService", "Students"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "$filter",
                  "value": "status eq 'ACTIVE'"
                },
                {
                  "key": "$select",
                  "value": "firstName,lastName,email"
                },
                {
                  "key": "$orderby",
                  "value": "lastName asc"
                },
                {
                  "key": "$top",
                  "value": "10"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Combined query: Filter active students, select specific fields, sort by name, limit to 10 results."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "OData V4 query options examples: $filter, $select, $orderby, $top, $skip, $count."
    },
    {
      "name": "Authentication (Cloud)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get OAuth2 Token (Client Credentials)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set('accessToken', jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('Token obtained and saved to environment');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "client_credentials",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{clientId}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{clientSecret}}",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{xsuaaUrl}}/oauth/token",
              "host": ["{{xsuaaUrl}}"],
              "path": ["oauth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Get OAuth2 access token using client credentials flow.\n\n**For Cloud environment only.**\n\nThe token is automatically saved to the `accessToken` environment variable.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Get XSUAA credentials from `cf env student-manager-srv`\n2. Set `xsuaaUrl`, `clientId`, `clientSecret` in Cloud environment"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get OAuth2 Token (Password Grant)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set('accessToken', jsonData.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('Token obtained and saved to environment');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "password",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "{{clientId}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "client_secret",
                  "value": "{{clientSecret}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "username",
                  "value": "{{username}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "password",
                  "value": "{{password}}",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{xsuaaUrl}}/oauth/token",
              "host": ["{{xsuaaUrl}}"],
              "path": ["oauth", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Get OAuth2 access token using password grant flow (user credentials).\n\n**For Cloud environment only.**\n\nThe token is automatically saved to the `accessToken` environment variable.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Set `username` and `password` with your SAP BTP user credentials\n2. Note: Password grant may not be enabled for all XSUAA configurations"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "OAuth2 authentication endpoints for SAP BTP Cloud Foundry.\n\n**Usage:**\n1. Select 'Cloud (BTP)' environment\n2. Configure XSUAA credentials from `cf env student-manager-srv`\n3. Run 'Get OAuth2 Token' request\n4. Token is auto-saved to `accessToken` variable\n5. Other requests will use the token via Bearer auth\n\n**Not needed for Local environment** (uses Basic Auth)."
    },
